# AGENTS.md Creation Protocol

**When working on any agent project, always create and maintain an AGENTS.md file.**

## When to Create AGENTS.md

Create `AGENTS.md` in the project root when:
- Starting a new agent/assistant project
- Adding AI capabilities to existing project
- Working with LLM integrations (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
- Implementing Agent Lightning training

## AGENTS.md Template

```markdown
# AGENTS.md

## Agent Overview
- Purpose: [What does this agent do?]
- Model: [gpt-4o, claude-sonnet-4-20250514, etc.]
- Framework: [OpenAI Agents, LangChain, custom, etc.]

## Architecture
- Entry point: [main file]
- Tools: [list of tools/functions]
- Memory: [how context is managed]

## Training (Agent Lightning)
- Traces: [where traces are stored]
- Reward function: [how success is measured]
- Prompts: [versioned prompt location]

## Instructions for AI Agents
[Compressed docs index and key instructions for the agent]

IMPORTANT: Prefer retrieval-led reasoning over pre-training-led reasoning.
```

## Connection to Agent Lightning

When AGENTS.md exists, integrate with training:

1. **Document reward signals** in AGENTS.md
2. **Track prompt versions** referenced in training/prompts/
3. **Log architecture decisions** for training context
4. **Update after training runs** with performance improvements

## Why AGENTS.md Matters

Per Vercel research: AGENTS.md (passive context) achieves 100% pass rate vs 53% for skills alone. Always include key instructions directly in AGENTS.md rather than relying on skill invocation.

See also: `agent-lightning.mdc` for training patterns.
